  "market_context": "ETH consolidated through the Asia and London sessions, building sell stops below the Asia session lows. As price approached the New York open, it swept those sell-side lows, setting up a potential smart money reversal at a discount level.",
  "key_observation": "After sweeping sell-side liquidity below the Asia lows, price closed over the series of down-close candles to validate a smart money reversal order block; on the retracement, a second down-close candle into a fair value gap was closed through, forming a continuation order block with improved risk-to-reward.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify that price consolidated through Asia and London with sell stops resting below the Asia lows as the draw on liquidity into New York open.",
    "Step 2: Watch New York open sweep the sell-side liquidity below the Asia lows, putting price into a discount level for a potential reversal.",
    "Step 3: Wait for a close over the series of down-close candles that swept the lows to validate the smart money reversal order block.",
    "Step 4: Note that entering at the order block opening price with stop on the low only yields ~1.4R targeting the failure swing highs, which is insufficient.",
    "Step 5: Look instead for a continuation entry — a down-close candle into the next important level (fair value gap) above the reversal.",
    "Step 6: Wait for price to close over the bodies of those down-close candles, validating a second (continuation) order block.",
    "Step 7: Enter on the opening price of the continuation order block with stop on the swept low, targeting the failure swing highs for approximately 2R.",
    "Step 8: Alternatively mark the mean threshold (50% of body high to body low) of the order block to enter tighter and significantly improve risk-to-reward."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price reached the failure swing highs, delivering approximately 2R on the continuation order block entry (and ~2.6R if entered at the mean threshold).",
  "lessons": "After a smart money reversal, do not force an entry on the initial reversal order block if risk-to-reward is poor. Wait for a continuation order block — a down-close candle into a fair value gap that gets closed through — to align with the new bullish bias at improved R:R.",
